                    "name": "Haywire",
                    "text": "A severely damaged mechanical carny has a chance of malfunctioning. If a mechanical carny has 15 or fewer Hit Points at the start of its turn, it must succeed at a DC 5 flat check or go haywire. A haywire mechanical carny wildly attacks the nearest living creature, or the nearest object if no creatures are nearby. It takes a \u20131 circumstance penalty to Strikes but deals an additional 1d6 bludgeoning damage plus <a aonid=\"20\" game-obj=\"MonsterAbilities\">Knockdown</a>. This effect lasts 10 minutes or until the mechanical carny is destroyed."
